    "Name": "Taipan TPN-90",
    "Details": "The TPN-90 is a contemporaneous variant of the base Taipan developed for integration into Word of Blake C3 network formations. The Streak SRM 2 launcher and its ammunition are removed and replaced with a rear-right-leg-mounted Improved C3 Computer, contributing networked targeting data to allied units while the twin Light PPCs and MASC system remain unchanged from the TPN-89. The trade of independent close-range firepower for formation coordination reflects the Word of Blake's doctrine of combined-arms C3 warfare.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Improved Jammer</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 0.98</color></b>\n\n<color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limits: Left Upper, Right Upper</color>",
